## [Unreleased]

- Added Tauri plugin-opener integration and improved version management.
- Enhanced Tauri v2 environment detection with better error handling for a smoother experience.
- Updated the application to version 0.5.3, rebranding it with improved branding elements.

## [v0.5.3] - 2025-12-14

- Integrated Tauri plugin-opener and bumped the version number for enhanced compatibility.
- Improved environment detection in the Tauri v2 system, reducing errors during startup.
- Updated application to version 0.5.3, rebranding it with a fresh look and feel.

## [v0.5.2] - 2025-12-14

- Fixed issues with Tauri-based persistence layer retrieval for legacy data without JSON parsing.
- Implemented a more robust Tauri-based persistence layer that combines hybrid storage capabilities for better efficiency.

## [v0.5.1] - 2025-12-14

- Adjusted Phase Shift position in the Orbiting Models to improve visibility and user experience.

## [v0.5.0] - 2025-12-14

- Enhanced EMP settings with customizable radius, visual radius, and speed attributes for better gameplay control.
- Improved pause dialog instructions and removed automatic resume on escape key press for a more deliberate gaming experience.
- Replaced portal audio effects with new sky ship spawn sounds, removing unused effects for cleaner audio management.
- Updated tower spawning logic to use level configurations for max towers and levels limits, streamlining deployment processes.
- Simplified shield bar transitions for improved performance and visual appeal.
- Rounded player health values for a cleaner UI display, reducing confusion during gameplay.
- Adjusted shield recharge rates and tower parameters for balanced gameplay that keeps matches exciting and unpredictable.
- Added glow effects for hacked and disabled towers with new colors and pulsing animations to differentiate between different types of adversaries.
- Enhanced visuals for hacked and disabled towers by adjusting opacity and managing glow states effectively, making them more noticeable on the battlefield.
- Prevented EMP from occluding objects behind it by disabling depth write, ensuring clear visibility during critical moments in combat.
- Added a team-specific color parameter for EMP explosions to help players identify the origin of these powerful attacks quickly.
- Implemented infinite ammo toggle and updated related mechanics to offer players more strategic options during intense battles.
- Introduced visual effects for hacked towers with glow and color updates to signify their altered state dynamically.
- Implemented EMP and Hack Spike mechanics with comprehensive state management, allowing for a more immersive and challenging gameplay experience.
- Added last hit direction prop to the Game component, providing valuable feedback on enemy movements and attacks.

## [v0.4.0] - 2025-12-12

- Refactored MenuMusic by moving context to a separate file and updating imports for better modularity and maintainability.
- Redesigned SystemArchives layout and display of version information, enhancing user understanding of game updates.
- Enhanced UI components across SystemArchives, TeamSelectionDialog, and others, improving consistency and aesthetic appeal.
- Implemented Context for music control within MenuMusic, Home, and Game components, offering a more seamless audio experience.
- Integrated BackgroundEffects component into SystemArchives to provide enhanced visual feedback during gameplay.
- Adjusted tooltip positioning and spacing in OrbitingModels and TeamSelectionDialog, ensuring better visibility and interaction with UI elements.
- Enhanced Model Tooltips across SystemArchives and TeamSelectionDialog, along with adding navigation buttons for improved user navigation within the interface.
- Renamed CornerModels to OrbitingModels and updated their layout for improved consistency and usability across the application.

## [v0.3.0] - 2025-12-12

- Expanded copilot instructions and updated steering documentation for better onboarding and support.
- Added comprehensive unit tests for utility functions and weapon systems, ensuring code reliability and performance stability.
- Introduced a new sky ship spawn sound in audio settings, replacing old portal effects for a more immersive auditory experience.
- Updated tower hit hack sounds and integrated them into game logic, enhancing the feedback players receive during combat encounters.
- Slowed down the rotation speed of Hack Spike rings while adjusting their animations, improving visual clarity and gameplay enjoyment.
- Updated geometry and materials for Tower and User models, increasing visual fidelity and realism in-game.
- Added 3D preview components for both Tower and User models to aid in spatial understanding and strategic planning within the game.